The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Indians begin with easy win

New Delhi: Indian boys kicked off their junior Davis Cup campaign in style, blanking the UAE 3-0 in group III of the Asia-Oceania zone qualifiers in Manila. 

According to information received here, Agnel Gladwin opened with a 6-2, 6-1 win over Faisal Bastaki. Then Kinshuk Sharma clinched the tie with a 6-4, 6-0 defeat of Hamad Ismail before Sharma and Navneeth Kannan whipped Ismail and Khaled al Hassani 6-2, 6-0 to complete the sweep. 

India are seeded sixth in the under-16 competition featuring 18 countries which have been divided into five groups. 

 (PTI) 




